# =============================================================================
# Approach B (source rebuild) — see MODULE.bazel for the full rationale.
#
# wpa_supplicant / wpa_cli / wpa_passphrase are rebuilt from the SONiC fork
# (git submodule sonic-wpa-supplicant/) so wpa_supplicant carries the SONiC
# `macsec_sonic` driver (CONFIG_DRIVER_MACSEC_SONIC=y). The object lists and
# -D flags below were harvested verbatim from the upstream wpa_supplicant
# Makefile via `make -n all` under debian/config/wpasupplicant/linux (the
# `.config` used by src/wpasupplicant/sonic-wpa-supplicant/debian/rules
# override_dh_auto_build). This guarantees the rebuilt binary compiles the
# exact same translation units with the exact same feature macros as the Make
# baseline (target/debs/trixie/wpasupplicant_2.9.0-14_amd64.deb).
#
# The macsec_sonic driver adds two objects — driver_macsec_sonic.c (C) and
# sonic_operators.cpp (C++, includes <swss/...>) — and links libswsscommon +
# libstdc++ (drivers.mak: DRV_LIBS += -lswsscommon -lstdc++). libswsscommon and
# libnl come from the migrated @sonic-swss-common and @libnl3 modules; openssl,
# dbus, pcsclite, readline, ncurses come from @wpa_deps (apt -dev packages).
# =============================================================================

# Feature macros, harvested from `make -n all` (CONFIG_* -> -D...). Identical
# for every translation unit (wpa's Makefile puts them in the global CFLAGS).
# NOTE on the two string-valued macros (shell-quoting in the Makefile recipe
# collapses one layer of quotes):
#   * -DLOG_HOSTAPD="$(CONFIG_DEBUG_SYSLOG_FACILITY)"  -> gcc sees the *token*
#     LOG_DAEMON (the shell strips the quotes), so we pass -DLOG_HOSTAPD=LOG_DAEMON.
#   * -DTLS_DEFAULT_CIPHERS=\"$(CONFIG_TLS_DEFAULT_CIPHERS)\" with
#     CONFIG_TLS_DEFAULT_CIPHERS="DEFAULT@SECLEVEL=1" -> gcc sees the C *string*
#     literal "DEFAULT@SECLEVEL=1", so we keep the embedded quotes.
